id: pm-v7dj
title: Add agent-optimized pm plan command with linked dependencies
description: "Design and implement a first-class built-in Plan item type plus pm plan command family that mirrors Codex, Claude Code, and Cursor planning surfaces while reusing pm item history, search, dependencies, ownership, and progressive-disclosure outputs."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[6]: agent-ux,context-efficiency,plan,planning,pm-cli,progressive-disclosure
created_at: "2026-05-17T08:39:33.695Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:53:09.478Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Built-in Plan item type exists and --type plan resolves to Plan; Plan items are stored in normal pm item storage with full history hash-chain tracking; plan metadata captures scope, harness provenance, ordered steps, step links, decisions, discoveries, validation, and resume context; pm plan create/show/add-step/update-step/complete-step/block-step/link/materialize/approve expose agent-optimized workflows; steps can link pm dependencies and related items; outputs default to low-token TOON with JSON/fields/depth projections; search indexes Plan scope/steps/decisions/discoveries/dependencies; SDK/MCP/plugins/docs/dogfood cover Codex/Claude/Cursor-style usage; focused tests and isolated dogfood prove behavior."
parent: pm-rnpb
